The paper deals with fundamental problems related to hash functions and expander graphs, which are topics commonly studied in computer science. The use of space-time tradeoffs and efficient recursive constructions suggests a focus on data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The construction of expander graphs involves graph theory and combinatorics (cs.CG), while the analysis of time bounds suggests a focus on complexity theory (cs.CC) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
